Summary of CWE:
This happens when too much data is placed into a fixed-size buffer, which can overwrite memory.

b. Example C code:

char buffer[5];
strcpy(buffer, "too long text");

c. Remediation (fixed code):

strncpy(buffer, "safe", sizeof(buffer)-1);
buffer[sizeof(buffer)-1] = '\0';

Explanation:
Limit how much data is copied into buffers.

d. Mitigation and detection:
Use safe functions, input validation, and security tools.
